---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import "../css/projects.css";
---

<Layout>
  <header class="project-header">
    <h1 class="page__title">Wildlife Rescue & Operations Platform</h1>
    <p class="page__subtitle">Solutions Engineering & System Design</p>
  </header>
  <section class="section__container">
    <h2 class="section__title">1. Problem & Goals</h2>
    <p class="section__intro">
      Campaign page creation was a manual, cross-team process that led to
      inefficiencies, delays, and inconsistent data.
    </p>

    <ul class="section__list --parent">
      <li class="section__item">
        Campaign page creation relied on manual coordination between sales,
        frontend, and announcements teams
      </li>
      <li class="section__item">
        Workflow was fragmented:
        <ul class="section__list">
          <li class="section__item">Communication via chat tools (Chatwork)</li>
          <li class="section__item">
            Manual extraction and rewriting into tickets
          </li>
          <li class="section__item">
            Manual duplication of templates and folders
          </li>
          <li class="section__item">Inconsistent and hard-to-track data</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li class="section__item">
        Impact:
        <ul class="section__list">
          <li class="section__item">6–8 hours to prepare a single page</li>
          <li class="section__item">
            8–15 back-and-forth messages per project
          </li>
          <li class="section__item">
            Frequent inconsistencies and information loss
          </li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li class="section__item">
        Goals:
        <ul class="section__list">
          <li class="section__item">
            Reduce manual coordination and repetitive work
          </li>
          <li class="section__item">Standardize input and data handling</li>
          <li class="section__item">Improve delivery speed</li>
          <li class="section__item">Scale from ~16 to 30+ projects/month</li>
          <li class="section__item">
            Maintain quality through controlled automation
          </li>
        </ul>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="section__container">
    <h3 class="section__subtitle">Before vs After</h3>
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Aspect</th>
          <th>Before</th>
          <th>After</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>Setup time</td>
          <td>6–8h</td>
          <td>2–4h</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Communication</td>
          <td>8–15 messages</td>
          <td>Minimal</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Data consistency</td>
          <td>Low</td>
          <td>High</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </section>

  <section class="section__container">
    <h2 class="section__title">2. Context & Constraints</h2>
    <p class="section__intro">
      The solution operates within a cross-team, semi-technical environment and
      must respect both technical limitations and business realities.
    </p>

    <ul class="section__list --parent">
      <li class="section__item">
        Environment:
        <ul class="section__list">
          <li class="section__item">
            Cross-functional workflow (Sales, Frontend, Design, Announcements)
          </li>
          <li class="section__item">Non-technical users providing input</li>
          <li class="section__item">Asynchronous collaboration across teams</li>
        </ul>
      </li>

      <li class="section__item">
        Technical constraints:
        <ul class="section__list">
          <li class="section__item">No direct AI access to internal systems</li>
          <li class="section__item">
            Script-based execution (no backend services)
          </li>
          <li class="section__item">
            Use of existing tools (Google Sheets, Drive, Gemini AI)
          </li>
        </ul>
      </li>

      <li class="section__item">
        Business constraints:
        <ul class="section__list">
          <li class="section__item">
            Frontend-driven ecosystem (Node.js preferred)
          </li>
          <li class="section__item">Small team (2 members)</li>
          <li class="section__item">Fast adoption with minimal disruption</li>
          <li class="section__item">Cost efficiency vs scaling headcount</li>
        </ul>
      </li>

      <li class="section__item">
        Assumptions:
        <ul class="section__list">
          <li class="section__item">AI can structure semi-structured input</li>
          <li class="section__item">
            Human validation is required before publishing
          </li>
          <li class="section__item">
            Structured data improves consistency and scalability
          </li>
        </ul>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="section__container">
    <h3 class="section__subtitle">System Context</h3>
    <img
      src="/images/pagegen_diagram_systemboundries.jpg"
      alt="System Context Diagram"
    />
  </section>

  <section class="section__container">
    <h2 class="section__title">3. Users & Requirements</h2>

    <ul class="section__list --parent">
      <li class="section__item">
        Users:
        <ul class="section__list">
          <li class="section__item">Sales team (input campaign data)</li>
          <li class="section__item">
            Frontend engineers (generate and validate pages)
          </li>
          <li class="section__item">
            Announcements team (content and tracking)
          </li>
        </ul>
      </li>

      <li class="section__item">
        Functional requirements:
        <ul class="section__list">
          <li class="section__item">
            Accept unstructured or semi-structured input
          </li>
          <li class="section__item">Convert input into structured JSON</li>
          <li class="section__item">Classify project type and templates</li>
          <li class="section__item">Generate HTML from templates</li>
          <li class="section__item">Store and share data across systems</li>
        </ul>
      </li>

      <li class="section__item">
        Non-functional requirements:
        <ul class="section__list">
          <li class="section__item">Maintainability (Node.js ecosystem)</li>
          <li class="section__item">Consistency (single source of truth)</li>
          <li class="section__item">Security (no direct AI execution)</li>
          <li class="section__item">Usability (non-technical input support)</li>
          <li class="section__item">Reliability (fallback without AI)</li>
          <li class="section__item">
            Scalability (increasing campaign volume)
          </li>
        </ul>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="section__container">
    <h2 class="section__title">4. System Overview</h2>
    <p class="section__intro">
      The system is designed as an AI-assisted pipeline separating data
      structuring, execution, and validation.
    </p>

    <ul class="section__list --parent">
      <li class="section__item">AI processing (input structuring)</li>
      <li class="section__item">Script-based execution</li>
      <li class="section__item">Human validation</li>
    </ul>

    <h3 class="section__subtitle">System Flow</h3>
    <ol class="section__list --parent">
      <li class="section__item">Sales provides input (Google Sheets)</li>
      <li class="section__item">AI transforms data into structured JSON</li>
      <li class="section__item">JSON becomes the source of truth</li>
      <li class="section__item">CLI generates pages</li>
      <li class="section__item">Frontend validates output</li>
      <li class="section__item">Pages are deployed</li>
    </ol>

    <img src="/images/pagegen_diagram_flow.jpg" alt="System Flow Diagram" />
  </section>

  <section class="section__container">
    <h2 class="section__title">5. Architecture</h2>

    <ul class="section__list --parent">
      <li class="section__item">AI Processing (Gemini)</li>
      <li class="section__item">Data Layer (JSON)</li>
      <li class="section__item">Automation Layer (Apps Script)</li>
      <li class="section__item">Storage (Sheets, Drive)</li>
      <li class="section__item">Output (HTML, Markdown)</li>
      <li class="section__item">Human Validation</li>
    </ul>

    <img src="/images/pagegen_diagram_c2.jpg" alt="C2 Architecture Diagram" />

    <h3 class="section__subtitle">Core Pipeline (Representative)</h3>
    <pre><code class="language-json">
  function processRow(sheet, row)&#123;
    const lock = LockService.getScriptLock();
    try &#123;
      lock.waitLock(5000);
      // simplified
    &#125; finally &#123;
      lock.releaseLock();
    &#125;
  &#125;</code></pre>
  </section>

  <section class="section__container">
    <h2 class="section__title">6. Data Model & Behavior</h2>

    <ul class="section__list --parent">
      <li class="section__item">
        Project Management Data:
        <ul class="section__list">
          <li class="section__item">Stored in Google Sheets</li>
          <li class="section__item">
            Contains campaign metadata and ownership
          </li>
          <li class="section__item">Tracks project lifecycle</li>
        </ul>
      </li>

      <li class="section__item">
        Page Management Data:
        <ul class="section__list">
          <li class="section__item">Stored in Google Sheets</li>
          <li class="section__item">Defines page configuration and tracking</li>
          <li class="section__item">
            Includes links, status, and delivery info
          </li>
        </ul>
      </li>

      <li class="section__item">
        Page Generation Data (Source of Truth):
        <ul class="section__list">
          <li class="section__item">Structured JSON used for generation</li>
          <li class="section__item">Decouples content from implementation</li>
          <li class="section__item">
            Enables consistent and repeatable outputs
          </li>
        </ul>
      </li>
    </ul>

    <pre><code>&#123;
  "template": "store_osaka",
  "page_path": "osaka_store",
  "store": "osaka",
  "title": "Manga in Osaka store",
  "sales_period_start": "2026/03/01",
  "sales_period_end": "2026/05/30",
  "post_sales_allowed": true
  &#125;</code></pre>

    <h3 class="section__subtitle">CLI Prototype</h3>
    <pre><code>node src/generator.js --file shibuya.json</code></pre>
  </section>

  <section class="section__container">
    <h2 class="section__title">7. Decisions & Trade-offs</h2>

    <ul class="section__list --parent">
      <li class="section__item">
        AI limited to structuring (reliability over flexibility)
      </li>
      <li class="section__item">
        JSON as source of truth (strict schema required)
      </li>
      <li class="section__item">Node.js ecosystem (simple and maintainable)</li>
      <li class="section__item">Human-in-the-loop validation</li>
      <li class="section__item">Apps Script simplicity vs scalability</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="section__container">
    <h2 class="section__title">8. Reliability & Scalability</h2>

    <h3 class="section__subtitle">Reliability</h3>
    <ul class="section__list --parent">
      <li class="section__item">Input validation</li>
      <li class="section__item">Script validation</li>
      <li class="section__item">Frontend review</li>
      <li class="section__item">Fallback without AI</li>
    </ul>

    <h3 class="section__subtitle">Scalability</h3>
    <ul class="section__list --parent">
      <li class="section__item">Current: Sheets + scripts</li>
      <li class="section__item">
        Future: backend service + database + dashboard
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="section__container">
    <h2 class="section__title">9. Outcome & Learnings</h2>

    <h3 class="section__subtitle">Impact</h3>
    <ul class="section__list --parent">
      <li class="section__item">6–10h → 2–4h preparation time</li>
      <li class="section__item">Reduced communication overhead</li>
      <li class="section__item">Scaled to 30+ projects/month</li>
    </ul>

    <h3 class="section__subtitle">Outcome</h3>
    <ul class="section__list --parent">
      <li class="section__item">Standardized workflow</li>
      <li class="section__item">Improved data consistency</li>
      <li class="section__item">Foundation for internal platform</li>
    </ul>

    <h3 class="section__subtitle">Learnings</h3>
    <ul class="section__list --parent">
      <li class="section__item">
        AI works best for structuring, not execution
      </li>
      <li class="section__item">Workflow design improves team efficiency</li>
      <li class="section__item">Human validation increases reliability</li>
      <li class="section__item">Structured data enables scalability</li>
    </ul>
  </section>
</Layout>
